---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About LrGeniusAI — Free & Open Source AI Plugin for Lightroom Classic"
  description="LrGeniusAI is a free, open-source AI plugin for Lightroom Classic. Learn about the project's mission, local-AI-first philosophy, AGPL-3.0 license, and how to contribute."
>

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://lrgenius.com" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "About", "item": "https://lrgenius.com/about" }
    ]
  })} />

  <section class="hero compact">
    <h1>About LrGeniusAI</h1>
    <p class="tagline">Free, open-source AI for every Lightroom Classic photographer.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="about-section">
    <h2>What is LrGeniusAI?</h2>
    <p>
      LrGeniusAI is a plugin for Adobe Lightroom Classic that brings modern AI capabilities directly into your
      photo management workflow — without requiring a subscription, a cloud account, or any photos leaving your
      computer. It covers AI keywording, natural-language photo search, AI-assisted culling, face recognition,
      and experimental editing recipes, all from inside Lightroom.
    </p>
    <p>
      The plugin is free and open-source under the
      <a href="https://www.gnu.org/licenses/agpl-3.0.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">AGPL-3.0 license</a>.
      Source code lives on <a href="https://github.com/LrGenius" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="about-section">
    <h2>Why free and open-source?</h2>
    <p>
      The tools photographers need to organize and find their work should not cost a monthly subscription on top
      of an already expensive software stack. AI models powerful enough to describe and search photos now run on
      consumer hardware — there is no technical reason these features should require a cloud subscription.
    </p>
    <p>
      By releasing LrGeniusAI under the AGPL-3.0 license, the project commits to staying free and open.
      Anyone can inspect the code, adapt it, or contribute improvements. Derivative works must also remain
      open under the same terms — ensuring that the community's contributions stay in the commons.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="about-section">
    <h2>Local AI first</h2>
    <p>
      LrGeniusAI is designed to run your photos entirely on your own hardware via
      <a href="/help/docs/help-ollama-setup">Ollama</a> or <a href="/help/docs/help-lm-studio-setup">LM Studio</a>.
      When running locally, no image data ever leaves your computer — no telemetry, no training on your
      photos, no third-party access. This matters for photographers working with unpublished client work,
      sensitive subjects, or simply anyone who values owning their data.
    </p>
    <p>
      Cloud providers (ChatGPT, Google Gemini, Google Vertex AI) are also supported for those who want
      maximum model quality or don't have suitable hardware for local inference. The choice is always yours.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="about-section">
    <h2>Status and roadmap</h2>
    <p>
      LrGeniusAI is under active development. Core features — AI keywording, semantic search, and face
      recognition — are stable and in daily use by photographers. AI culling and editing recipes are in
      beta and still maturing.
    </p>
    <p>
      Installers are currently not code-signed, which may trigger security warnings on macOS and Windows.
      This is a known limitation that will be addressed as the project matures.
      See the <a href="/help/docs/getting-started">Getting Started guide</a> for current installation
      instructions and the <a href="/help/docs/faq">FAQ</a> for common questions.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="about-section">
    <h2>How to contribute</h2>
    <p>
      Contributions of all kinds are welcome — bug reports, feature requests, documentation improvements,
      or code. The project is hosted on GitHub:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="https://github.com/LrGenius/LrGeniusAI/issues" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Report a bug or request a feature</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://github.com/LrGenius/LrGeniusAI/discussions" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Ask questions and share ideas</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://github.com/LrGenius" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Browse the source code</a></li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      If LrGeniusAI saves you time, consider starring the repository on GitHub — it helps others discover
      the project.
    </p>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
  .hero.compact {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 3rem 0 1rem;
  }
  .tagline {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: #666;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }
  .about-section {
    padding: 2rem 0;
    border-top: 1px solid #eaeaea;
    max-width: 720px;
  }
  .about-section h2 {
    margin-top: 0;
    color: var(--color-primary, #0066cc);
  }
  .about-section p, .about-section li {
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: #333;
  }
  .about-section ul {
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }
  .about-section li {
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }
</style>
